libcircle
------------------------------------------
An API to provide an efficient distributed queue on a cluster. Libcircle is
currently used in production to quickly traverse and perform operations on a
file tree which contains several hundred-million file nodes.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libcircle-devel-0.3-1bl2
  libcircle2-0.3-1bl2
  libopenmpi40-4.1.6-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  libopenmpi-devel-4.1.6-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/hpc/libcircle/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/hpc/libcircle/archive/refs/tags/v0.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libcircle-0.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libcircle-0.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libcircle-0.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcircle-0.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcircle2-0.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcircle-devel-0.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libcircle)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libcircle.README
  /usr/share/doc/libcircle/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libcircle/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libcircle/HACKING.md
  /usr/share/doc/libcircle/README.md

(libcircle2)
  /usr/bin/cygcircle-2.dll

(libcircle-devel)
  /usr/include/libcircle.h
  /usr/lib/libcircle.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libcircle.pc

